Package org.github.fussel178.telestion.extension.corfu.corfu.mapper.store

Interface MessageTypeStore

All Known Implementing Classes:
GlobalStore, HashMessageTypeStore
public interface MessageTypeStore

Description

The message type store acts as a translation layer between name or id of a corfu component and the actual JVM class type that represents the corfu component.

Currently, the following components can be translated:

  • CorfuNode
  • CorfuHardware
  • CorfuAppTelemetry
  • AppTelemetryPayload
  • CorfuAppTelecommand
  • AppTelecommandPayload

The HashMessageTypeStore is the current reference implementation of the message type store.

Usage

 
 // resolve by name
 var nodeTypeByName = store.getNodeType("obc");
 System.out.println(nodeTypeByName.getSimpleName()); // ObcNode

 // resolve by id
 var nodeTypeById = store.getNodeType(0x13);
 System.out.println(nodeTypeById.getSimpleName()); // ObcNode

      void registerNode​(Class<? extends CorfuNode> nodeClassType, String nodeName, short nodeId, Class<? extends CorfuHardware> hardwareClassType)
      Registers a new Corfu node class that should be accessible through the store.
      Parameters:
      nodeClassType - the class type of the new node
      nodeName - the name of the node as defined in the Corfu configuration
      nodeId - the id of the node as defined in the Corfu configuration as unsigned byte
      hardwareClassType - the class type of the hardware the node provides

    • registerTelemetryPayload

      void registerTelemetryPayload​(Class<? extends AppTelemetryPayload> payloadClassType, String payloadName, short payloadId, short nodeId, Class<? extends CorfuAppTelemetry> associatedTelemetryApp)
      Registers a new telemetry payload for an already registered Corfu app that should be accessible through the store.
      Parameters:
      payloadClassType - the class type of the new telemetry payload
      payloadName - the name of the payload as defined in the Corfu configuration
      payloadId - the id of the payload as defined in the Corfu configuration as unsigned byte
      nodeId - the associated node id of this payload (useful for standard telemetry) Note: Return CorfuPayload.ANY_NODE_ID if the payload is not associated to any node.
      associatedTelemetryApp - the associated Corfu telemetry app Note: The app should be registered with registerAppTelemetry(Class, String, short) first.
